ies significant (> 50%) variability for about 47% and 14% at 12.2 GHz and\n6.7 GHz, respectively. This difference can be explained via the standard model\nof methanol masers.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 25 Mar 2021 16:21:02 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-04-28"}
